postcontent:
2nd Gen Glock 23 in .40 S&W
Factory Night Sights
4 Drop free GLOCK magazines
Blackhawk CQC holster
13 rounds (1 full mag) of 180gr Remington Golden Saber HP self defense ammo
Hogue palm swell textured grip sleeve
Grip plug
Tritium Night Sights
Low Round Cound


This is a great package.  

The 2nd gen Glock was the best!  Look around; you wont find many because they've been swiped up.  This gun is meant for carry so no rail needed (try to find a concealed carry holster that accepts a light/laser and doesn't print).  The 2nd gen has a more tapered muzzle area so it's a faster draw and easier to reholster.  The grip is textured with no grooves so any hand will fit.  Because this was my carry gun it has holster wear.  Glock will refinish it for $50 but these aren't meant to be pretty so no need.  I have put less than 500 rounds through the gun and I always cleaned and maintained it.  87 of those rounds were Rem 180gr Golden Saber.  I made sure they ran in the gun and kept the last 13 of the 100 for carry.  I'm including them because this gun loves them and now you don't have to spend $100 to test SD loads.  Sights are still pretty bright - I'd say at least 80% because I actually can't tell the difference from the new ones on my 1911.  This gun handles recoil very well and is extremely accurate.  

I called Glock and they said just drop it in a UPS or FedEX box and mail to them with a check.  You get it back in new condition in about 2 weeks.  Like I said though, carry guns get rub marks and Glocks are built for reliability not beauty so it was not a priority for me.

BTW The holster has the paddle attachment - I just forgot to put it on for the photo.  You will get that too.

title: For Sale:  Tikka 1927 Stepped, "A" Marked Barrel M91
postcontent:
Good condition 1927 Finnish M91, with a very rare "A" marked stepped barrel. Less than 3,000 of the stepped barrel variation were made, and the "A" marked barrel is a rare and desirable variation of this small number.

The normal, non-A marked stepped barrel 1927 Tikka M91 is listed as a "9" rarity on 7.62x454R.net:
http://7.62x54r.net/MosinID/MosinRarity.htm

Rifle has a gouge in the stock near where the shooter's dominant palm. Metal and wood is about 70% or better overall. Bore is excellent. The rifle is very accurate; with my limited skills, it's shot 3-4" at 100 yards on the bench with Bulgarian surplus.

I am looking for a collector to sell this to. The rifle is rare enough that it deserves to be in a collection and shot rarely. Don't be afraid to bid, as my definition of "collector" is quite flexible.

I will post pictures as soon as I gain the use of a decent camera.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Taser C2 With laser
postcontent:
I have a brand NEW sealed in the package black Taser C2 with the built in laser. The taser comes with the battery, 1 cartridge, manual and training DVD. I am asking $275.00, academy sports and Bass Pro shops are selling the same taser package for $349.99 plus tax. I am also interested in trades let me know what you have? 




From Taser's web site:
The technologically advanced TASER C2 is designed for your personal safety needs. Utilizing the same technology as our proven law enforcement models, it offers incredible take down power and unparalleled protection right in the palm of your hand.

TASER C2 is an Electronic Control Device (ECD) that delivers an incapacitating pulse that overrides the sensory and motor functions of the nervous system. This powerful Neuro Muscular Incapacitation (NMI) technology can stop even the most aggressive individuals, including those under the influence of drugs and/or alcohol.

The C2 uses a replaceable cartridge containing inert, compressed nitrogen to fire two small probes that are attached to 15 foot (4.5 meter) insulated conductive wires. Energy is sent over the wires into the probes, which can penetrate up to two cumulative inches of clothing. The charge is transmitted between the two probes, jamming sensory and motor functions, and inhibiting muscular control. This NMI effect continues in 30-second cycles each time you press the trigger. The C2 can also be used as a direct contact stun device.


Advanced Features
15 ft. (4.5 m) range allows you to stop an attacker before s/he gets to you 
30 second electrical pulse allows you time to safely escape danger or keep an attacker down 
Bold laser sighting system helps you aim confidently and accurately 
Integrated LED light illuminates dark places to improve your line of vision 
Compact, lightweight design allows it to be easily and discreetly carried everywhere you go 
Long-lasting Lithium Power Magazine allows over 50 uses, ensuring you have power when you need it most

The technologically advanced TASER C2 is designed for your personal safety needs. Utilizing the same technology as our proven law enforcement models, it offers incredible take down power and unparalleled protection right in the palm of your hand.

TASER C2 is an Electronic Control Device (ECD) that delivers an incapacitating pulse that overrides the sensory and motor functions of the nervous system. This powerful Neuro Muscular Incapacitation (NMI) technology can stop even the most aggressive individuals, including those under the influence of drugs and/or alcohol.

The C2 uses a replaceable cartridge containing inert, compressed nitrogen to fire two small probes that are attached to 15 foot (4.5 meter) insulated conductive wires. Energy is sent over the wires into the probes, which can penetrate up to two cumulative inches of clothing. The charge is transmitted between the two probes, jamming sensory and motor functions, and inhibiting muscular control. This NMI effect continues in 30-second cycles each time you press the trigger. The C2 can also be used as a direct contact stun device.
